By BO Staff Writer President Jacob Zuma has released the much talked about Terms of Reference of the Judicial Commission of Inquiry into State Capture. While some were calling for the president to keep the Terms of Reference within the scope of the State of Capture report by Thuli Madonsela (i.e. only focusing on the Gupta and Zuma families), anti-white monopoly capital activists have been calling for the expansion of the terms to include corruption by white capital. Read the full document, originally published on the Government Gazette, below: 369960575-Terms-of-reference-for-Commission-on-State-Capture-Inquiry 